HEADWORD: CBC
<hw>CBC</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the complete blood count; a clinical
test which counts the number of white and red blood cells and the number
of platelets in one cubic millimeter of blood.</def>
<mark>[acronym]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> complete blood count, blood profile.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

